/**
 * @file translations-data.mjs
 *
 * Hand-authored translations for keys that were still rendering English
 * across pt/es/fr/de/ja/ko/zh because the sync-i18n-keys.js fallback had
 * never been replaced with real localised content.
 *
 * Conventions:
 *  - Brand and product nouns stay verbatim across every locale: AgentOS,
 *    Frame, Wunderland, Paracosm, GMI, GitHub, Discord, LinkedIn, Twitter,
 *    Slack, Telegram, WhatsApp, OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Ollama, Postgres,
 *    SQLite, Qdrant, Pinecone, Neo4j, Docker, Kubernetes, Vercel, Railway,
 *    Fly.io, Pinecone, HyDE, GraphRAG, Ebbinghaus, Louvain, HNSW, HEXACO,
 *    Whisper, Deepgram, ElevenLabs, AssemblyAI, Apache 2.0, MIT, Node.js.
 *  - Acronyms stay verbatim: API, APIs, SDK, SDKs, CLI, DAG, RAG, HEXACO,
 *    FAQ, PII, STT, TTS, DSL, GDPR, SOC 2, OSS, JSON, OpenAPI, MMR.
 *  - Code/identifiers stay verbatim: @framers/agentos, npm install ...,
 *    function names like discover_capabilities, hitl.llmJudge(), etc.
 *  - Email addresses (team@frame.dev) and URLs stay verbatim.
 *  - Numbers / percentages keep en-US numeric format (no locale separator
 *    swaps) to match the source code that injects metric values.
 *  - HEXACO trait labels translate to the conventional psychology terms in
 *    each language; the HEXACO acronym itself does not.
 *
 * The merge script (scripts/translate-locales.mjs) protects any value
 * already different from en.json from being overwritten, so re-running is
 * idempotent and safe.
 */

